******
[2]
Date: Tue 17 Sep 2019, 08:19 PM
Source: KazInform [edited]
https://www.inform.kz/en/four-people-diagnosed-with-anthrax-in-zhambyl-region_a3566591


Four residents of Zhambyl region have been diagnosed with anthrax. This was confirmed by the Regional Public Health Protection Department, Kazinform correspondent reports. On [12 Sep 2019], 4 residents of Zhambyl and Zhualy municipalities sought medical treatment at the regional infectious diseases hospital. All of them complained of wrist inflammation, malignant pustules, papules and soft tissue edemas around the wound.

"Three patients were initially diagnosed with erysipelas. However, in order to rule out anthrax, the contents of the wound were sent to a special laboratory of the Sanitary Inspection Center. Anthrax was confirmed for all the 4 patients," Berik Zharkynbekov, Head of the Regional Public Health Protection Department, said. All the patients are receiving appropriate treatment now.

According to Berik Zharkynbekov, all 4 patients participated in slaughtering anthrax-infected animals; 2 of them work as shepherds at Surym farm in Zhualy municipality and 2 are wage workers. As many as 44 individuals who were in close contact with them are under medical supervision now.

