[I included the third report as it demonstrates where our US tax dollars go. This latter report indicated possible gastroenteric infections, while the 2 previous local reports had typical cutaneous lesions on the hands and forearms. If the four men had been slaughtering and butchering sick cattle as is hinted, such cutaneous lesions are very typical. The search for any affected source cattle appears to have been perfunctory.

Zhambyl is in the midst of an area of Kazakhstan where livestock anthrax occurs. For a description of Zhambyl, go to: http://spktaraz.kz/eng/jambul/ and: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jambyl_Region. To confirm we are in the right part of Kazakhstan on the southern border with Kyrgyzstan, go to Zhualy, the paired district: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zhualy_District. - Mod.MHJ

